Miranda Kerr and Evan Spiegel have welcomed their first child together - a baby boy named Hart. TMZ reports the model gave birth at Cedars-Sinai Medical Centre in LA around 23:50 on Monday night. Mom and baby are happy, healthy and resting at home, E! News confirmed. Miranda and Evan tied the knot in an intimate garden ceremony in May. The 33-year-old model announced her engagement to the 26-year-old via Instagram in July 2016. A family spokesperson confirmed Miranda's pregnancy in November, saying: "Miranda, Evan and Flynn are looking forward to welcoming the newest member of their family." Baby Hart is Miranda's second child. She shares custody of 6-year-old son Flynn Christopher Bloom with ex-husband Orlando Bloom. Source: Channel24